1. bash prep/version-check.sh
2. bash prep/library-check.sh
3. create partition for LFS
4. sudo mkdir /mnt/lfs
5. sudo prep/mount.sh #or manually mount your new partition to /mnt/lfs
6. sudo prep/sudo.sh

might want to reboot here.  

1. sudo prep/mount.sh #or manually mount your new partition to /mnt/lfs
2. su - lfs
3. ./main.sh


